<subSubSection id="15D2BA9D2126BA1FD2C79E0905BDAF05" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph id="E4AED9CE561772FD33506356EA6CDC40" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DF7359907AF72C0BD1D892E6AF548D6" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Herb, annual or rarely perennial, achlorophyllous, holoparasitic. Stems fleshy. Leaves reduced to scale-like bracts. Inflorescences terminal racemes, spikes, corymbs, or panicles. Calyx 5-toothed. Corolla sympetalous, bilabiate to regular, tubular and often curved. Style long, stigma crateriform and peltate, or bilamellar. Fruit loculicidal capsules.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F2410DB758526989B8B2CE2CAABC91D" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">About 22 species: 18 in North America, 4 in South America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
